    "To assess the effect of new knowledge in D on the performance of M D, we have to annotate each (q, a) pair in D w.r.t.",
    "whether M knows that the answer to q is a. foot_4 To estimate this, we define a continuous P Correct measure based on samples from M, and use it to divide (q, a) pairs into four knowledge categories.",
    "We name this approach SliCK (Sampling-based Categorization of Knowledge).",
    "Defining P Correct.",
    "We adopt the perspective that M knows that the answer to q is a if it generates a when prompted to answer q (Kadavath et al., 2022; Manakul et al., 2023)."
